        <td rowspan="2">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box2">Pressure Angle : <text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; font-style:italic;">μ</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">It is the angle from the &#160;instantaneous normal force acting on the cam-follower by the cam (or visa-versa), and the instantaneous velocity vector of the center of the Cam-Follower.</para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box2">Contact Pressure Angle : <text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; font-style:italic;">μ</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; font-style:italic; vertical-align:baseline;">c</text></para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName-small">Not normally used) <text styleclass="Popup Box">The angle, </text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; font-style:italic;">μ</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; font-style:italic; vertical-align:baseline;">c,</text><text styleclass="Popup Box"> between the instantaneous normal force acting on the cam-follower by the cam (or visa-versa), and the instantaneous velocity vector of the </text>contact point<text styleclass="Popup Box"> of the Cam-Follower with the cam.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box2">ONLY USE THIS WHEN THE CAM-FOLLOWER MUST SLIDE.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
